FOUR residents have been arrested in connection with the murder of Kutlwano Kasibe. The 16-year-old, who was mentally challenged, was allegedly tied to a tree and doused with ice water before being sjambokked and shocked with a car battery. He was then dragged and dumped on the side of the road, where his mum found him after residents claimed he stole a tap. Daily Sun published the article on Wednesday, 22 June. And thereafter, four suspects, aged between 30 and 40, were arrested. Kutlwano’s mum, Dorah, was hoping that the arrest would serve as an example to other murderers. “I haven’t been able to sleep since my son’s passing. He didn’t deserve to be killed so gruesomely,” she said. Kutlwano’s burial is expected to take place on Saturday, but the family is facing financial difficulties. Dorah is unemployed and the family was surviving on Kutlwano and his sister’s grants. “The closer we get to the date, the angrier I become. ALSO READ |
Teen shot with his own gun! “We have a society but it doesn’t cover everything.” Some members of the community revealed threats in their WhatsApp group. A source said: “Most residents are rallying behind those arrested and calling for R20 each towards bail.” Another source said: “Some are sending threats against people who called cops and alerted Daily Sun. They say they need to be dealt with if found.” Dorah said it broke her heart even more to hear that the community was supporting those arrested. Lieutenant-Colonel Mavela Masondo said the suspects would appear in the Protea Magistrates Court on Friday, 24 June.